<br>
RE: Attention Whore<br>
<br>
I'll just get this one out of the way first, since it makes me peevish.  I looked up &quot;gay elves&quot; for signature ideas, because shockingly my character is a gay elf.  Well, a cat now, but that is due to a storyline development and is still actually a half-elf who happens to be cursed. I saw the sig, found it edgy, and decided to use it as it fits my personality.  <br>
<br>
The fact that the signature predictably caused this controversy is irrlevant.  When I first started using the signature, some people commented and I temporarily changed my signature to a disgustingly cute kitten which ... *gasp* also got lots of comments about how cute it was.  I chose the kitten photo for two reasons: 1. as satiric commentary on signature debates, and 2. to show that I respected the FV community enough to place my signature aside until the moderators made a decision.  I guess if people really want to they can say that I chose it because I am an attention whore, after all I picked a kitten that was just *too* cute.<br>
<br>
Anyway, after not too much time Ceilo declared that neither mine nor Robin's signatures were pornographic and the topic was locked and I assumed the issue dealt with.  If you want you can go to the dead horse forum and check the post called &quot;Pornography, anyone?&quot; that started with Robin and ended with Ceilo.  That new people see the signature and raise the issue again and again is by no means any attempt on my part to get attention, especially when it's already dead-horsed.  Then why did I start this thead, you might ask?  Because my signature was randomly brought into a discussion and no longer had the opportunity to address it then and there.<br>
<br>
And in my opinion, the fact that signatures of this sort get so much attention and that similar ones of staight couples get significantly less attention demonstrates the need for more exposure to these issues.  Relatedly, the similarities between Robin and I end with us both being gay and educated.  I in no way attempt to mimick him - I am my own person and will continue to be so.  In fact Robin and I have clashed on several issues in the past.  If I was trying to be a Robin-groupie I'd just mindlessly agree with his commentary be on my merry way.<br>
<br>
RE: LAWYER QUESTION/OFFENDING<br>
<br>
No, Kurley, I would not place photos of gay cartoon elves in my office because such photos have no place there.  A law office is a professional environment and such photos would be out of place.  This is NOT to say that I would not put up other photos - such as black and white artistic photos of two men kissing, or holding hands, or something of a similar nature if I found it classy.  ((This environment is in stark contrast to an EverQuest messageboard featuring a wide array of edgy signatures.  Even so, I generally refrain from posting my signature aside from in the SoapBox - usually not including my signature in the General Forum or on my guild's messageboard.))<br>
<br>
One of the things I've decided after my first year of law school was that I would never sacrifice my individuality for anyone or anything.  I've spent my whole life being told what to do, what to wear, who to be friends with ... and now that I'm on my own I will forever be who I want to be.  If who I happen to be offends people - then that is their problem not mine because I am not a doll people can dress and pose however they want.<br>
<br>
If this signature offends some people - then I am sorry but it is not going to change until I find something else that appeals to me.  I am not here to please each and every one of you because I already know, just living my every day life, that it is simply not possible.  I can walk down the street holding my boyfriends hand and have two girls be like &quot;aww how cute&quot; and then turn the corner and have a rock thrown at me.  I can leave a store in the city where fellow customers help me pick out a trendy new outfit and feel totally boss only to walk out the door and hear a guy on a motorcycle drive by screaming &quot;fag!&quot;  None of this is new to me, and if I'm thankful for my thick skin. <br>
<br>
-Gio<br>
